wikipedia_page.main: Robert Oswald Milne (10 September 1852 – 6 September 1927) was an English cricketer active in 1882 who played for Lancashire. He was born in Prestwich and died in Leamington Spa. He appeared in one first-class match and scored seven runs with a highest score of 7*.
